# Environment — Simple Roster Plus (repo root)

Copy to `.env` in this directory and adjust.

```bash
# PostgreSQL connection string used by Prisma (e.g. Neon)
DATABASE_URL="postgresql://USER:PASSWORD@localhost:5432/simple_roster_plus?schema=public"
# Direct URL for migrations. On Neon with a pooler DATABASE_URL, use the non-pooler host here
# (or omit locally — migrate-deploy derives it from DATABASE_URL when the host contains -pooler).
# DIRECT_URL="postgresql://USER:PASSWORD@ep-xxx.us-east-1.aws.neon.tech/neondb?sslmode=require"

# Session JWT signing — required for login (min 16 characters; use a long random string in production)
AUTH_SECRET="dev-only-change-me-to-at-least-sixteen-chars"

# Operator console (platform admin plane at /ops; see docs/OPERATOR_CONSOLE.md). SEPARATE
# secret from AUTH_SECRET so the operator and tenant token pools cannot cross-validate.
# Min 16 chars. Operator sign-in is disabled until this is set.
OPERATOR_AUTH_SECRET="dev-only-operator-secret-at-least-sixteen-chars"

# Optional: serve the operator console on its own subdomain. Any host starting with
# "admin." is treated as the operator plane automatically; set ADMIN_HOST only to match an
# exact non-"admin."-prefixed host. The customer app stays on app.* / your primary domain.
# ADMIN_HOST="admin.simplerosterplus.com"

# --- Stripe (billing; source of truth for money). See docs/OPERATOR_CONSOLE.md §3.2. ---
# Server-side secret key. Use sk_test_... in dev/preview, sk_live_... in production.
# Operator billing reads and the "Sync from Stripe" action are disabled until this is set.
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY="sk_test_xxx"
# Webhook signing secret (whsec_...) from the Stripe endpoint pointing at /api/stripe/webhook.
# Required to verify and accept webhook events.
STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SIGNING_SECRET="whsec_xxx"
# Publishable key for client-side Stripe.js (tenant checkout, future). Safe to expose.
NEXT_PUBLIC_STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY="pk_test_xxx"
# One-time: npm run stripe:seed-products — creates lookup_key prices per docs/PRICING.md

# Public HTTPS base for ADMS pairing copy (device push/poll URLs). Per-org override on Devices
# (AppSetting public_app_url) wins over these; then VERCEL_URL on Vercel; then request host in dev.
# Also used as the canonical app host when redirecting off simplerosterplus.vercel.app.
# APP_URL="https://app.simplerosterplus.com"
# NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL="https://app.simplerosterplus.com"

# Optional ZKTeco handshake tuning (minutes east of UTC in device option block; default -240)
# ZK_ICLOCK_TIMEZONE_OFFSET_MINUTES=-240
# Set to 0 to omit TimeZone from GET /iclock/cdata handshake
# ZK_ICLOCK_HANDSHAKE_TIMEZONE=1

# --- Marketing site (landing-page contact / early-access form) ---
# Comma-separated origins allowed to POST /api/marketing/contact (static landing CORS).
# MARKETING_ALLOWED_ORIGINS="https://www.simplerosterplus.com,https://simplerosterplus.com,http://127.0.0.1:5500"
# Inbox for optional Resend notifications (submissions are always stored in MarketingInquiry).
# MARKETING_CONTACT_TO="hello@simplerosterplus.com"
# RESEND_API_KEY="re_xxx"
# MARKETING_CONTACT_FROM="Simple Roster Plus <hello@simplerosterplus.com>"

# --- Welcome email (new Clerk account provisioning; see lib/email/welcome.ts) ---
# Uses RESEND_API_KEY. Skipped when the key is unset. Sent once when a new AppUser row is created.
# WELCOME_EMAIL_FROM="Simple Roster Plus <hello@simplerosterplus.com>"
# SUPPORT_EMAIL="hello@simplerosterplus.com"

# --- Operator signup alerts (new org owner provisioned; see lib/email/signup-notify.ts) ---
# Inbox for Resend notifications when someone self-serves signup. Falls back to
# MARKETING_CONTACT_TO, then active OperatorUser emails when unset.
# Requires RESEND_API_KEY. Uses MARKETING_CONTACT_FROM when SIGNUP_NOTIFY_FROM is unset.
# SIGNUP_NOTIFY_TO="hello@simplerosterplus.com"
# SIGNUP_NOTIFY_FROM="Simple Roster Plus <hello@simplerosterplus.com>"

# --- WhatsApp roster alerts (Twilio) ---
# TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID="ACxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx"
# TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN="your-auth-token"
# TWILIO_WHATSAPP_FROM="+15617303361"
# Approved Call-to-action Utility template Content SID
# ({{1}} name, {{2}} week, {{3}} share token for button URL …/share/roster/{{3}}).
# See docs/WHATSAPP_ROSTER_TEMPLATE.md — CTA button, not plain Text with a full URL.
# TWILIO_WHATSAPP_ROSTER_CONTENT_SID="HXxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx"
# Optional: only if using temp Blob tools (not required for link notify).
# BLOB_READ_WRITE_TOKEN="vercel_blob_rw_..."
# Canonical HTTPS base for share links in WhatsApp messages (recommended in production).
# APP_URL="https://simplerosterplus.vercel.app"

# --- In-app tester feedback (design partners; see docs/mvp-launch/feedback-loop.md) ---
# Inbox for Resend notifications on each submission (submissions are always stored in TesterFeedback).
# FEEDBACK_CONTACT_TO="hello@simplerosterplus.com"
# Falls back to MARKETING_CONTACT_TO, then active OperatorUser emails when both are unset.
# Requires RESEND_API_KEY. Uses MARKETING_CONTACT_FROM when FEEDBACK_CONTACT_FROM is unset.
# FEEDBACK_CONTACT_FROM="Simple Roster Plus <hello@simplerosterplus.com>"

# Optional overrides for `npm run db:seed`
# SEED_ADMIN_EMAIL="admin@demo.local"
# SEED_ADMIN_PASSWORD="demo"
# SEED_ORG_NAME="Demo Organization"
# SEED_ORG_TIMEZONE="America/Toronto"
# SEED_OPERATOR_EMAIL="ops@demo.local"
# SEED_OPERATOR_PASSWORD="ops"

# Create or reset an operator console user without the full seed (production-safe):
#   PROVISION_OPERATOR_EMAIL="you@example.com" \
#   PROVISION_OPERATOR_PASSWORD="strong-password" \
#   npm run provision-operator
# Re-run with a new password to reset. Optional: PROVISION_OPERATOR_ROLE=superadmin

# --- Clerk (tenant self-serve auth; step 10 / Gate 2) ---
# NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY="pk_test_xxx"
# CLERK_SECRET_KEY="sk_test_xxx"
# CLERK_WEBHOOK_SIGNING_SECRET="whsec_xxx"
# NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_SIGN_IN_URL="/sign-in"
# NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_SIGN_UP_URL="/sign-up"
# NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_AFTER_SIGN_IN_URL="/setup"
# NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_AFTER_SIGN_UP_URL="/setup"

# --- Cron / maintenance (demo sandbox reclaim) ---
# CRON_SECRET="long-random-string"
# POST /api/cron/reclaim-demos with Authorization: Bearer $CRON_SECRET
# POST /api/cron/onboarding-followups with Authorization: Bearer $CRON_SECRET

# --- Onboarding funnel (docs/ONBOARDING_FUNNEL.md) ---
# Automatic follow-up emails stay off until explicitly enabled (Phase 5).
# ONBOARDING_AUTOMATION_ENABLED=false
# ONBOARDING_ABANDON_SIGNUP_HOURS=2
# ONBOARDING_ABANDON_WORKSPACE_HOURS=24
# ONBOARDING_ABANDON_EMPLOYEES_HOURS=24
# ONBOARDING_ABANDON_ROSTER_HOURS=48
# ONBOARDING_ABANDON_PUBLISH_HOURS=48
# ONBOARDING_ABANDON_INACTIVE_HOURS=72
# ONBOARDING_MAX_FOLLOW_UPS=3
# Manual recovery email. Uses RESEND_API_KEY; automatic sequences remain disabled.
# ONBOARDING_FOLLOW_UP_FROM="Simple Roster Plus <hello@simplerosterplus.com>"
# ONBOARDING_MANUAL_SEND_WINDOW_HOURS=6
# ONBOARDING_OPERATOR_SENDS_PER_HOUR=30
# Automatic sequence delays. Ignored while ONBOARDING_AUTOMATION_ENABLED=false.
# ONBOARDING_AUTOMATION_FIRST_HOURS=24
# ONBOARDING_AUTOMATION_SECOND_HOURS=72
# ONBOARDING_AUTOMATION_FINAL_HOURS=120
```

Default seed sign-in (local dev only): **admin@demo.local** / **demo** and **ops@demo.local** / **ops**.

**Production:** do not run `npm run db:seed` with defaults — seed is blocked when `NODE_ENV=production` or `VERCEL_ENV=production`, and `@demo.local` logins are rejected at the API. Use `npm run prod:remove-demo-creds -- --confirm` if demo rows exist in prod. See `docs/mvp-launch/prod-hardening-checklist.md`.

Do not commit real secrets. `.env` is gitignored; `.env.example` is safe to commit.
